"title": "5183: smell",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5183",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An aroma; God is pleased by the aroma of sacrifice, whether a literal sacrifice or the figurative offering of Christian service is a picture of its acceptability to him. Bad smells can indicate physical decay or the results of judgment. To be a stench to someone is to be held in contempt or hated by that person.</p>\n<h2>The aroma of sacrifice</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:21\">GEN 8:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:9\">LEV 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:2\">LEV 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:5\">LEV 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:31\">LEV 4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:15\">LEV 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:21\">LEV 6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:21\">LEV 8:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:13\">LEV 23:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:18\">LEV 23:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:14\">NUM 15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:24\">NUM 15:24</a> <em>offerings to be made for unintentional breaking of the LORD's commandments</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:17\">NUM 18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:2\">NUM 28:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:2\">NUM 29:2</a></p>\n<h3>Substances to create a pleasing smell</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:7-Exod30:8\">EXO 30:7–30:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:22-Exod30:29\">EXO 30:22–30:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:34-Exod30:38\">EXO 30:34–30:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:28\">EXO 35:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:29\">EXO 37:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:26-Exod40:27\">EXO 40:26–40:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:16\">NUM 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:4\">2CH 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:11\">2CH 13:11</a></p>\n<h3>The aroma of sacrifice is not always pleasing to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:31\">LEV 26:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:11-Ezek8:13\">EZK 8:11–8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:27-Ezek20:29\">EZK 20:27–20:29</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was the supreme fragrant offering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:2\">EPH 5:2</a></strong></p>\n<h2>God accepts his people as fragrant incense</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:41\">EZK 20:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:5-Hos14:6\">HOS 14:5–14:6</a></p>\n<h2>A pleasing aroma depicts acceptable Christian service</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:14-2Cor2:16\">2CO 2:14–2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:18\">PHP 4:18</a></p>\n<h2>Fragrance associated with the expression of love</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:2-Song1:3\">SNG 1:2–1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:16-Song5:1\">SNG 4:16–5:1</a></strong> <em>The beloved's garden is an image of her body.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:8\">PSA 45:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:12-Song1:13\">SNG 1:12–1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:6\">SNG 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:10-Song4:11\">SNG 4:10–4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:13\">SNG 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:8\">SNG 7:8</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:3\">JHN 12:3</a></strong></p>\n<h2>A bad smell</h2>\n<h3>Indicating decay</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:39\">JHN 11:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:20\">EXO 16:20</a> <em>Manna soon smelled bad if kept. This meant the Israelites had to trust God afresh for each day's supply.</em></p>\n<h3>As the result of God's judgment</h3>\n<p>The first plague on Egypt, which made the Nile smell bad:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:18\">EXO 7:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:21\">EXO 7:21</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:3\">ISA 34:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:10\">AMO 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>As a picture of the results of judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:24\">ISA 3:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:6\">ISA 19:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:20\">JOL 2:20</a></p>\n<h3>As a figurative cause of contempt or hatred</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:30\">GEN 34:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:21\">EXO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:4\">1SA 13:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:6\">2SA 10:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:6\">1CH 19:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:21\">2SA 16:21</a></p>\n<h2>Idols cannot smell</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:4-Ps115:6\">PSA 115:4–115:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:28\">DEU 4:28</a></p>",
